result.name: Tai Hing

reviews.text: Modern Hong Kong style food

Good chain providing Cantonese staples with some healthy options. Menu and prices vary throughout the day and the menu is a bit confusing as a result  - always check the availability times in tiny print near the top of the menu pages. Otherwise a good place for clean, quick meal or snack.

Tai Hing is famous for its barbecue meats. The main feature is the roast pig.  Unfortunately it’s not available all the time.  One doesn’t ah I’d like to recommend is the “pig lung” soup - it’s delicious and a must-try.  If you order just the soup it’s $49 per serving. But if you order it (plus a bowl of rice) as an add on to a regular dish you only pay an extra $29 - it’s a steal.  
Seafood vermicelli (served in a clay pot) is the best vermicelli dish I ever had.  Their sweet and sour pork is phenomenal.  Ask the server for recommendation. Try new dishes. You will be pleasantly surprised.
Hong Kong style coffee shop. Quite nice.

it has good clothing items and also make up booths. They also have pop up shops sometimes
